Header and Footer
---
title: "Document with logo"
header-includes: 
   - \usepackage{graphicx}
   - \usepackage{fancyhdr}
   - \pagestyle{fancy}
   - \setlength\headheight{28pt}
   - \fancyhead[L]{\includegraphics[width=5cm]{cynkra-logo.png}}
   - \fancyfoot[LE,RO]{GPIM}
   - \usepackage{fancyhdr}
   - \pagestyle{fancy}
   - \fancyhead[CO,CE]{This is fancy header}
   - \fancyfoot[CO,CE]{And this is a fancy footer}
   - \fancyfoot[LE,RO]{\thepage}
output: pdf_document
---

\addtolength{\headheight}{1.0cm} 
\fancypagestyle{plain}{} the first page
\thispagestyle{fancy} 
\fancyhead[L]{\includegraphics[width = 100pt]{cynkra-logo.png}}
\renewcommand{\headrulewidth}{0pt}

Customization points





Latex packages \usepackage{glossaries-extra}
Latex packages used by R packages; like \usepackage{longtable}
Advanced: Define new Latex environments

Customization points







cd_header &lt;- function(header_text_right = "",
                      header_text_left = "") {
  indiedown_glue(
   r"(
   \newcommand\hcrule[3][black]{\textcolor{#1}{\rule[-2mm]{#2}{#3}}}
   \thispagestyle{fancy}
   \fancyhead[LE]{\thepage \hcrule[dunkelorange]{.5mm}{7mm} &lt;&lt;header_text_right&gt;&gt;}
   \fancyhead[RO]{&lt;&lt;header_text_left&gt;&gt; \hcrule[dunkelorange]{.5mm}{7mm} \thepage}
   )")}

Convert the template
---
title: "Document with logo"
header-includes: 
   - \usepackage{graphicx}
   - \usepackage{fancyhdr}
   - \pagestyle{fancy}
   - \setlength\headheight{28pt}
   - \fancyhead[L]{\includegraphics[width=10cm]{logo_here.png}}
output: pdf_document
---

